Articles.Content:
Ever since the 0.90 update, I've been having issues with KW Rocketry 2.6d2. The thing is that parts are not showing up in the VAB, but flags are showing.

I have merged the GameData folder properly, updated to Module Manager 2.5.4, and did a clean install of KSP as well. I tried rolling back to Mod Manager 2.5.1, but that didn't work.

Attached below are some pictures showing that the KW Rocketry parts load on the loading screen, that the flags go in game, but none of the parts show up in game even if I sort by manufacturer (some members said that has worked). The other mods I have are as follows, all of which work fine.

-Kerbal Joint Reinforcement 2.4.5

-Infernal Robotics 0.19.3

-AIES 1.5.1

-Kerbal Engineer Redux 1.0.13

I should note that KW Rocketry was the first mod I attempted to install and had the issue then, so I don't believe it would be an incompatibility issue.

Loading screen:

Flag screen:

VAB (Sort by manufacturer):

I have gotten all of the parts to load into the VAB, this was after I loaded the Procedural Fairings mod; however whenever I attempt to add a KW part (ie an engine) to the ship, it will not connect, puffs of smoke will shoot out the side and all the boxes on the top right (such as load/save ship, launch, exit) will gray out, and I cannot move the ship at all. I'll have to CTRL+ALT+DEL out of the game to exit.

I am merging the GameData folder as I do with all other mods (move GameData to GameData, then click okay to merge when prompted).

Edited December 19, 2014 by skyfire322

No, move GameData to KSP (where the GameData folder is) and merge, or move the *stuff* in a mod's GameData folder into KSP/GameData and merge.

The way you're describing it, it sounds like you're putting a mod's GameData folder into KSP/GameData so you have KSP/GameData/GameData.
Thanks! I feel really silly now. :\ Cheers!

Everything is loading now! I'm now running into the issue to where whenever I attempt to add an RCS port, it will activate (as seen in the picture below) and the game will crash. The same thing happens with the fairings and engines as well. Could this be a parts compatibility issue?

Edited December 20, 2014 by skyfire322
Fixed. Deleted TweakScale, and all is well.
